<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,537,994]" pageId="8" pageNumber="459">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1891" box="[151,270,537,562]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Poecilimon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="459" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inflatus">
<emphasis box="[151,270,537,562]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="459">P. inflatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a narrow range in the south-west corner of Anatolia and its range is geographically very heterogeneous. Some other lineages restricted to the same area, exhibit interesting patterns of diversity and the Demre district seems to be special (
<bibRefCitation box="[549,741,609,634]" pageId="8" pageNumber="459" refId="ref17258" refString="Veith, M. E., Oz, M., Kiefer, A., Baran, I., Polymeni, R. M. &amp; Steinfartz, S. (2008) Cracking the nut: geographical adjacency of sister taxa supports vicariance in a polytomic salamander clade in the absence of node support. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution, 47, 916 - 931. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. ympev. 2007.11.017" type="journal article">
Veith 
<emphasis box="[617,665,609,634]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="459">et al</emphasis>
. 2008
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation box="[752,973,609,634]" pageId="8" pageNumber="459" refId="ref15450" refString="Boztepe, Z., Kaya, S. &amp; Ciplak, B. (2013) Integrated systematics of the Poecilimon luschani species group (Orthoptera, Tettigoniidae): radiation as a chain of populations in a small heterogeneous area. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 169, 43 - 69. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / zoj. 12058" type="journal article">
Boztepe 
<emphasis box="[851,907,609,634]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="459">et al.</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation box="[985,1175,609,634]" pageId="8" pageNumber="459" refId="ref16754" refString="Kaya, S., Boztepe, Z. &amp; Ciplak, B. (2015) Phylogeography of the Poecilimon luschani species group (Orthoptera, Tettigoniidae): a radiation strictly correlated with climatic transitions in the Pleistocene. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 173 (1), 1 - 21. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / zoj. 12202" type="journal article">
Kaya 
<emphasis box="[1051,1108,609,634]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="459">et al.</emphasis>
2015
</bibRefCitation>
). This speciality is also observed for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1891" box="[302,415,645,670]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Poecilimon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="459" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inflatus">
<emphasis box="[302,415,645,670]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="459">P. inflatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group and the extensive material showed that the Kemer-Demre population of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1891" box="[1323,1436,645,670]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Poecilimon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="459" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inflatus">
<emphasis box="[1323,1436,645,670]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="459">P. inflatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs morphologically from that in the remaining western part of the range. We decided to indicate this diversity to the taxonomy of species by defining the Demre population as a separate taxon. As reproductive isolation between these forms needs further testing we defined the latter population as a separate subspecies, 
<taxonomicName authority="Kaya &amp; Chobanov &amp; Heller &amp; Yahyaoğlu &amp; Uluar &amp; Çiplak, 2018" authorityName="Kaya &amp; Chobanov &amp; Heller &amp; Yahyaoğlu &amp; Uluar &amp; Çiplak" authorityYear="2018" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Poecilimon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="459" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="inflatus" status="subsp. n." subSpecies="lyciae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="459">P. inflatus lyciae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[230,340,789,814]" pageId="8" pageNumber="459" rank="subSpecies">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[230,340,789,814]" pageId="8" pageNumber="459">subsp. n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
Description of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1891" box="[530,646,789,814]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Poecilimon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="459" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inflatus">
<emphasis box="[530,646,789,814]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="459">P. inflatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was supplemented by 
<bibRefCitation box="[921,1078,789,814]" pageId="8" pageNumber="459" refId="ref15951" refString="Heller, K. G. (2004) Poecilimon martinae n. sp. and P. inflatus Brunner von Wattenywyl, 1891 (Orthoptera, Tettigonioidea, Phaneropteridae), two bush-cricket species endemic to southwest Anatolia: morphology, bioacoustics and systematics. Articulata, 19, 1 - 17." type="journal article">Heller (2004)</bibRefCitation>
and is also valid for the new subspecies except for the diagnostic characters.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,537,994]" pageId="8" pageNumber="459">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1913893128" country="Turkey" location="Aydin Province" pageId="8" pageNumber="459" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Aydin Province">
<bibRefCitation box="[199,376,861,886]" pageId="8" pageNumber="459" refId="ref16622" refString="Karabag, T. (1958) Orthoptera Fauna of Turkey (Turkiye'nin Orthoptera faunasi) Ankara Universitesi Fen Fakultesi Yayinlari, Ankara-Turkey, 98 pp." type="book">Karabağ (1958)</bibRefCitation>
reported this species from Bölüntü (
<collectingRegion box="[794,971,861,886]" country="Turkey" name="Aydin" pageId="8" pageNumber="459">Aydın Province</collectingRegion>
of 
<collectingCountry box="[1011,1093,861,886]" name="Turkey" pageId="8" pageNumber="459">Turkey</collectingCountry>
) on the basis of one male and one female. Although field studies by one of the authors (SK) has been done in this locality on the same date as reported no sample was found. This locality is far from the presently confirmed range of the species and needs confirmation. On the other hand it is difficult to assign it to any subspecies without examining the specimens.
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
